[{"id":"VR188305","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of two oppositely charged objects in a coordinate plane with the origin labeled O, vertical axis labeled y, and horizontal axis labeled x. The negatively charged object is shown near the leftmost point along the horizontal x axis. The positively charged object is shown near the rightmost point along the horizontal x axis. Both charges are equidistant from the origin. Point P is located near the top of the vertical y axis. Two dashed lines, each with a length of r, extend from the charges to Point P.\" height=\"162\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188305.g03.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two objects with charges of equal magnitude but opposite signs are fixed on the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-axis at the same distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> from point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure above. The magnitude of the electric field at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> due to the charges is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the magnitude of the electric field at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> if each charge is doubled?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR188305_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 E\"><math alttext=\"2 E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 times the square root of 2, end root, times E\"><math alttext=\"2 times the square root of 2, end root, times E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msqrt><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 E\"><math alttext=\"4 E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 times the square root of 2, end root, times E\"><math alttext=\"4 times the square root of 2, end root, times E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msqrt><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]